title: Ring, 1931-84-2, 19th century
medium: Silver, paste stones, two human teeth
dimensions: H x diam.: 2.3 x 2.6 cm (7/8 x 1 in.)
description: Silver ring said to be a memorial to a child. In a silver setting are two teeth surrounded by a ring of green and red paste jewels; one heart-shaped piece and two pieces in design of keys are attached to small rings on the ornament. Mark inside, indistinguishable.
